## 🚜 Arduino-Based Agricultural Weed Remover Cart

An Arduino-powered smart agricultural robot designed to automate weed removal in crop fields. The prototype aims to reduce manual labor, improve farming efficiency, and minimize the use of chemical herbicides through a simple and cost-effective robotic solution.

### 🔹 Features
- Arduino Uno-based control system
- Four-wheel drive using DC geared motors
- Front-mounted weed-removing mechanism
- Battery-powered operation
- Compact and lightweight prototype
- Expandable with Bluetooth, IoT, and obstacle detection

### 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Arduino Uno
- C/C++ (Arduino IDE)
- L298N Motor Driver
- DC Geared Motors
- Servo Motor
- Rechargeable Battery
- Cardboard Prototype Chassis

### 📌 Key Highlights
- Developed a low-cost agricultural automation prototype.
- Designed a robotic cart capable of removing weeds between crop rows.
- Reduced dependence on manual labor and chemical weed control.
- Built a modular design that can be upgraded with AI and IoT technologies.

### 🚀 Future Enhancements
- AI-based weed detection using a camera
- GPS-guided autonomous navigation
- Solar-powered charging system
- Mobile app control via Bluetooth/Wi-Fi
- IoT-based monitoring and analytics

